description:
This observation is for the chirping insect sounds, which I think are from a species of Crickets. ...

(I made a separate observation for the song from a Western Meadowlark [heard starting at about 00:02 seconds, in the same audio recording].) ...

Heard a bit south or SE of the South Trailhead, at Hankinson Hills Recreation Area, NW of Hankinson, ND.

This observation is for the trilled calls in the background of the audio recording, which I will place at the category for True Crickets. ...

(I made a separate observation for the loud, steady insect sounds throughout, which may be from a species of Katydids.) ...

(I also made a separate observation for what sounds like bird calls in the background, heard at about 4 seconds and again at 14 seconds into this recording, which I placed at the general category for Birds, but wonder if it might be from a large wading bird.) ...

Heard from the marshy area (with lots of Cattails) across the paved path, south of the parking lot, within Forest River Nature Park, in far south Fargo, ND.
